<div class="courseblock main">
<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>MUSI 17003.  Rockefeller Chapel Choir.  000 Units.</strong></p><p class="courseblockdesc">
The Rockefeller Chapel Choir and its professional subset, the Decani, sing at Sunday services and festivals throughout the academic year and also in Rockefeller's signature Quire &amp; Place concert series, presenting major works from the entire historical canon, lesser-known gems, and the premières of new work by distinguished composers. The choir's members come from diverse spiritual and cultural backgrounds, sharing together the rich musical experience of singing an array of choral music in the unique religious and cultural contexts of a chapel to which students of all world traditions are drawn.</p><p class="courseblockdetail">
Instructor(s): J. Kallembach     Terms Offered: Autumn
Spring
Winter<br/>
