<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>MUSI 17023.  Middle East Music Ensemble.  000 Units.</strong></p><p class="courseblockdesc">
The Middle East Music Ensemble explores a variety of classical, neo-classical, and popular musical forms from throughout the Middle East, encompassing compositional and improvisational techniques unique to non-Western musical culture. Members perform on traditional instruments, often in company with noted guest artists, and present multiple concerts both on and off campus. No previous experience in the genre is required, but the ability to read music is necessary. Membership includes students, faculty, and staff of the University, as well as community members interested in the art and music of the Middle East.</p><p class="courseblockdetail">
Instructor(s): W. Zarour     Terms Offered: Autumn
Spring
Winter<br/>
